// REGRESSION: the virtual-main (main.tks) calls a top-level fn defined in ANOTHER file of the
// same project, UNQUALIFIED. The self-hosted (.tks-compiled) engine previously failed here with
// "unknown function: use_counter" because type_program typed loose top-level statements with an
// empty cur_ns; the native C bootstrap always worked. Fixed by setting cur_ns per item.
if use_counter(21) != 42 { exit(1) }
